---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import ScrollReveal from "../components/ScrollReveal.tsx";
import { SITE } from "../config/site.mjs";
---

<Layout
	title={`Colophon | ${SITE.title}`}
	description="The tools, software and services I use to build and run this site"
	canonicalURL={`${SITE.url}/colophon/`}
>
	<Header />
	<main id="main-content" role="main">
		<section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-20">
			<ScrollReveal client:idle>
				<h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Colophon</h1>
			</ScrollReveal>
			<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.1}>
				<p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-12">
					The tools, software and services I use to build and run this site
				</p>
			</ScrollReveal>

			<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
			<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
				<h2>Overview</h2>
				<p>
					Having built built sites for a long time, I've always enjoy learning
					what makes sites tick to really understand the tools and methods used.
					One site,
					<a
						href="https://builtwith.com/"
						class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
						>BuiltWith</a
					> attempts to break that down on the fly to show you those breadcrumbs,
					and I've made it a habit to list what I use on my sites, so here are the
					tools, software and services I use to build and run Silverbeet.
				</p>
			</ScrollReveal>

			<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
				<h3>Colophon</h3>
				<ul>
					<h4>Tools & Software</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>
							<a
								href="https://www.alpinelinux.org/"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>Alpine Linux</a
							>: a security-oriented, lightweight Linux distribution based on
							musl libc and busybox
						</li>
						<li>
							<a
								href="https://astro.build/"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>Astro</a
							>: a javascript web framework for content-driven websites
						</li>
						<li>
							<a
								href="https://docker.com/"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>Docker</a
							>: an open platform for developing, shipping, and running
							applications. Bonus, here's my Docker
							<a
								href="https://github.com/silverbeet-technology/website/blob/main/compose.yml"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>compose.yml</a
							>: file for this site, and its associated
							<a
								href="https://github.com/silverbeet-technology/website/blob/main/.env"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>.env</a
							> environment file it reads during startup
						</li>
						<li>
							<a
								href="https://traefik.io/"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>Traefik</a
							>: an open-source reverse proxy and load balancer for HTTP and
							TCP-based applications that can automatically retrieve TLS
							certificates from services like Let's Encrypt
						</li>
						<li>
							<a
								href="https://zed.dev/"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>Zed</a
							>: a relatively new Open Source IDE, minimal code editor that I
							really enjoy
						</li>
					</ul>

					<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
						<h4>Services</h4>
						<ul>
							<li>
								<a
									href="https://fastmail.com/"
									class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
									>Fastmail</a
								>: fast, private email hosting for you or your business
							</li>
							<li>
								<a
									href="https://github.com/"
									class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
									>GitHub</a
								>: hosted git for source control in an open environment
							</li>
							<li>
								<a
									href="https://letsencrypt.org/"
									class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
									>Let's Encrypt</a
								>: a nonprofit providing free TLS certificates to more than 700M
								websites
							</li>
							<li>
								<a
									href="https://porkbun.com/"
									class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
									>Porkbun</a
								>: for domain name registration and DNS service
							</li>
							<li>
								<a
									href="https://vultr.com/"
									class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
									>Vultr</a
								>: worldwide cloud servers
							</li>
						</ul>
					</ScrollReveal>

					<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
						<h3>Interesting?</h3>
						<p>
							I hope that was interesting, for those following along, here's the
							<a
								href="https://builtwith.com/silverbeet.tech/"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>BuiltWith Silverbeet page</a
							> which lists a few extraneous bits it found running the site. If you'd like to discuss your site, application or infrastructure and how it could be setup, feel free to
							<a
								href="/contact/"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>contact</a
							> me to start a dialog.
						</p>
					</ScrollReveal>
				</ul>
			</ScrollReveal>
		</section>
		<Footer />
	</main>
</Layout>
